metadata.title: 5 Year Chart Scoring Including Optional Component Standards - 20211111 0219.pdf
metadata.notes: Final Version PDF containing USAF Fitness Assessment scoring tables (cardiorespiratory and muscular fitness) for males and females across 5-year age bands. JSON contains parsed tables and raw snippets for verification.

passing_requirements: achieve a composite point total ≥ 75 points
meet minimum point values for all components

summary_notes: Health Risk Category = low, moderate or high risk

muscular_fitness.notes: Columns: 1-min Push-ups (reps->points), 2-min Hand-Release Push-ups (reps->points), 1-min Sit-ups (reps->points), 2-min Cross-Leg Reverse Crunch (reps->points), Forearm Plank Time (mm:ss -> points). Top rows parsed; raw snippet included for full table verification.

passing_requirements: meet minimum point values for all components

notes: I parsed the run-time bracket tables for all age bands and included parsed top rows for muscular fitness for each band. Where the PDF shows very long row-by-row numeric tables I preserved the raw snippet citation (filecite markers) so you can cross-check exact rows. If you'd like, I can expand any specific group's muscular_fitness table into a complete row-by-row array (CSV/JSON export) — tell me which age group(s) to fully expand and I'll output the full numeric list.
